grown-up TEM4

1. N-COUNT A grown-up is an adult. 成年人 

例： Jan was almost a grown-up. 简几乎是个大人了。 

2. ADJ Someone who is grown-up is physically and mentally mature and no longer depends on their parents or another adult. 长大成人的 

例： I seem to have everything anyone could want–a good husband, a lovely home, grown-up children who're doing well. 我似乎拥有任何人想要的一切–好丈夫,可爱的家和已长大成人、有出息的子女。 

3. ADJ If you say that someone is grown-up , you mean that they behave in an adult way, often when they are in fact still a child. 似成人的 

例： She's very grown-up. 她非常成人化。 

4. ADJ Grown-up things seem suitable for or typical of adults. 适于成人的 [非正式] 

例： Her songs tackle grown-up subjects. 她的歌曲以成人题材为主题。

